In the first part, the last cell of the second row is filled with five. In the second part, the middle cell of the second row is filled with zero. In the third part, the first cell of the second row is filled with five.

A2: A2: The corresponding output for each position of the 5x5 square in the input grid is determined by the pattern observed in the examples. [[4, 4, 4, 6, 6, 6, 3, 3, 3], [4, 4, 4, 6, 6, 6, 3, 3, 3], [4, 4, 4, 6, 6, 6, 3, 3, 3]]


Q3: Identify the rule for assigning numbers to each section of the output grid.
A3: A3: The rule for assigning numbers to each section of the output grid seems to be based on the position of the sections in the input grid. The first section (leftmost) of the output grid is filled with 4, the second section (middle) is filled with 6, and the third section (rightmost) is filled with 3. This pattern is consistent across all the examples provided.


Q4: Apply the rule identified in Q3 to the input grid of the quiz to generate the output grid.
A4: A4: Applying the rule identified in Q3 to the input grid of the quiz, the output grid would be:

[[4, 4, 4, 6, 6, 6, 3, 3, 3], [4, 4, 4, 6, 6, 6, 3, 3, 3], [4, 4, 4, 6, 6, 6, 3, 3, 3]]
